          "Created By:"
        ],
        [
          "A tremere from the last court, you were put in to torpor, for crimes vs the clan, but it was not recorded before the last chantry was attacked. Having just awoken up your trying to prove yourself enough incase your past ever comes out.",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "POT/RJ"
        ],
        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "You were always quiet and bookish, and so becoming a librarian seemed like such a natural thing for you. You worked your way up, becoming assistant to the head librarian of the Los Angeles library system - and you might have eventually even gotten that job for yourself, if your skills at organizing and cataloging information hadn't attracted the attention of the Tremere clan. You spent several years as a Tremere ghoul, tracking down and obtaining valuable books for your regnant. After a particulraly harrowing adventure involving stealing a collection of papers from the basement of an illegal club in Montreal, your regnant found you worthy of the Embrace and brought you over. You transitioned from mortal librarian to vampire librarian, tending the chantry's library, and reading what you could in your spare time. You weren't necessarily ambitious, but knowledge is power and before long, you had quite a lot of subtle influence in the clan (it helped that you were the keeper of the keys to the kingdom - someone who angered you would have a difficult time getting ahold of the book they needed for their research). Your unlife took a twist when Stanislaus Grey, your mentor within the clan, came to you with an alarming proposition. He intended to defect to the Sabbat, where his talents and skills would, he felt, be put to more use. He invited you to come with him, but you turned him down. You did, however, facilitate his escape from the Camarilla in LA, and helped him at least make contact with the Sabbat. You returned to the chantry with a story of being raided by Sabbat, and said you'd seen Grey die. You're not sure if you were believed or not, and feared that the chantry's regent would start a more formal investigation. Before any of that could happen, though, the Second Anarch War happened in Los Angeles in 1944, and the chantry was destroyed. You fell into torpor during the fighting, and have only recently awoken. You suspect that Grey is still out there, somewhere, and if he ever turns up, you know you'll be in trouble."
        ],
        [
          "Sire:",
          "Stanislaus Grey",
          "Reference: (If any)",
          "",
          "",
          "Clan",
          "Tremere - Easily Bound"
        ],
        [
